# Frontend Stack

- React + TypeScript.
- State management: Zustand (or similar lightweight store).
- HTTP client: Axios or Fetch wrapper.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS or CSS Modules (be consistent across project).

# Structure (Frontend)

- `frontend/src/components/` — reusable UI components (cards, forms, tables).
- `frontend/src/pages/` — pages that compose components into full views.
- `frontend/src/services/api.ts` — API client functions.
- `frontend/src/stores/` — Zustand stores (orders, tasks, work centers, UI state).
- `frontend/src/hooks/` — custom hooks (e.g., `useOrders`, `useTasks`).

# General Rules

- Each React component in its own file, default export.
- Keep components focused and small; factor out subcomponents if needed.
- Use **function components** with hooks; do not use class components.
- Types:
  - Use TypeScript interfaces/types for props.
  - Reuse generated or shared DTO types where possible (aligned with backend schemas).

# MES UI Concepts

Provide clear MES-oriented UI components:

- `OrderForm` — create manufacturing orders.
- `OrderList` — list and filter orders by status.
- `WIPDashboard` — visualize Work-in-Process and task queues.
- `TaskCard` — show details of a single ProductionTask.
- `TaskDetails` — show full history and genealogy for a task.
- `WorkCenterStatusPanel` — state of each work center.
- `QualityForm` — capture quality inspection data.

# API Integration

- All API calls go through `frontend/src/services/api.ts`.
- Handle error cases and map backend envelopes `{ success, data, error }` to UI states.
- Do not hardcode URLs inside components; inject them via api module or environment variables.

# Example: MES Frontend Component

Use this pattern when generating new React components.

```tsx
import React, { useState } from "react";
import { createOrder } from "../services/api";

interface OrderFormProps {
  onCreated?: () => void;
}

export const OrderForm: React.FC<OrderFormProps> = ({ onCreated }) => {
  const [productId, setProductId] = useState("");
  const [quantity, setQuantity] = useState<number>(1);
  const [orderNumber, setOrderNumber] = useState("");
  const [dueDate, setDueDate] = useState("");
  const [isSubmitting, setIsSubmitting] = useState(false);
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);

  const handleSubmit = async (event: React.FormEvent) => {
    event.preventDefault();
    setIsSubmitting(true);
    setError(null);

    try {
      const response = await createOrder({
        productId,
        quantity,
        orderNumber,
        dueDate,
      });

      if (!response.success) {
        setError(response.error ?? "Failed to create manufacturing order");
      } else if (onCreated) {
        onCreated();
      }
    } catch (e) {
      setError("Unexpected error while creating manufacturing order");
    } finally {
      setIsSubmitting(false);
    }
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="space-y-4 p-4 border rounded-md bg-white">
      <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold">Create Manufacturing Order</h2>

      {error && <div className="text-red-600 text-sm">{error}</div>}

      <div>
        <label className="block text-sm mb-1">Product ID</label>
        <input
          className="w-full border rounded px-2 py-1"
          value={productId}
          onChange={(e) => setProductId(e.target.value)}
          required
        />
      </div>

      <div>
        <label className="block text-sm mb-1">Quantity</label>
        <input
          type="number"
          className="w-full border rounded px-2 py-1"
          value={quantity}
          min={1}
          onChange={(e) => setQuantity(Number(e.target.value))}
          required
        />
      </div>

      <div>
        <label className="block text-sm mb-1">Order Number</label>
        <input
          className="w-full border rounded px-2 py-1"
          value={orderNumber}
          onChange={(e) => setOrderNumber(e.target.value)}
          required
        />
      </div>

      <div>
        <label className="block text-sm mb-1">Due Date</label>
        <input
          type="date"
          className="w-full border rounded px-2 py-1"
          value={dueDate}
          onChange={(e) => setDueDate(e.target.value)}
          required
        />
      </div>

      <button
        type="submit"
        disabled={isSubmitting}
        className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700 disabled:bg-gray-400"
      >
        {isSubmitting ? "Creating..." : "Create Order"}
      </button>
    </form>
  );
};